The reason for this is that the pathogens of sexually transmitted diseases can also be transmitted by lubricating infection or by close body contacts.
Experts therefore recommend that anyone who frequently changes sexual partners to undergo regular examinations.
Most rapidly detected STIs can be cured and late sequelae can be avoided.
